Yen Extends Declines Against Dollar, Euro Amid Economic Growth Differences

-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 
2011-04-03T22:25:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/yen-extends-declines-against-dollar-euro-amid-economic-growth-differences.html
The yen fell, extending last week’s
declines versus the dollar and the euro, amid signs central
banks in  Europe  and the U.S. are closer to raising interest
rates as the global economy recovers.  Japan ’s currency weakened to 84.35 per dollar as of 7:23
a.m. in  Tokyo  from 84.06 on April 1 in  New York . The yen slid to
119.99 against the euro from 119.66.  To contact the reporter on this story:
